social_posts.post_text: A little bonus content for you guys. Taylor has an incredible memory and I decided to test that out. Spoiler - he’s really good. Click the link in my bio for the full episode!

The Cayman Islands 🇰🇾 are actually a group of three islands located in the Caribbean, with Grand Cayman being the largest and most populated. Its filled with incredible food, hospitable people, and way more Canadians than I expected. 10/10 highly recommend
Connor Brown on Free Agency and possibly one day playing with Connor McDavid again. Full episode, Sunday June 25th. Link in Bio #NHL #Oilers #Podcast
Had a great chat with Seattle Kraken forward and 40 goal scorer Jared McCann and I had to ask him about the Cale Makar hit that knocked him out of the Colorado series. #NHL #hockey #podcast

The inside story of the goalie fight that almost was between Jordan Binnington and Marc-Andre Fleury on a chaotic night in St. Louis.

Watch the full interview with the Blues netminder Sunday on the Mitts Off podcast with @lukegazdic, available on YouTube, Spotify, Apple and all major streaming platforms."

Mullett Arena, 700 games, and a Gordie Howe hat trick. Full interview with Anaheim Ducks 🦆 centre Ryan Strome Thursday on Mitts Off!

I’ll never forget my first week playing in Stockton California in the minors. It came with a police warning. Watch the full interview with my former teammate and current Calgary Flames forward Andrew Mangiapane Sunday on Mitts Off
Getting lit up by John Tortorella was a weekly occurrence…and Nick Foligno absolutely loved it. Full interview with the Chicago Blackhawks forward out Monday on @mittsoffpod !

Owen Tippett loves a couple things - scoring goals, his family, and tattoos (and his dog). The Philadelphia Flyers forward walks me through his arm sleeve and the inspiration for it. Great player, even better guy. Full interview Tuesday on @mittsoffpod !
#nhl #nhlflyers

*Warning: This post does contain some sensitive material*
The fall of Brady Leavold was rapid. From WHL star to NHL training camp to being homeless and into the depths of addiction. To understand his incredible recovery, you need to go back to where it started. 
This was a tough, heavy conversation, but it’s why I started doing this in the first place. Brady is changing lives and I’m excited for his story to be shared. Full Interview Sunday on @mittsoffpod
